# Git Commit Author (stack-wide)

All repositories under the suherman.net stack must commit as **Iman Suherman** with email **iman.suherman@gmail.com** — author **and** committer.

Stack repos: `suherman-net-infra`, `urp-ct-mcp-studio`, `diskwise-macos`, `nucleus`, `iman-suherman`, `ops-shell-scripts`, `video-hub`, `macmini-fleet-manager` (paths in `suherman-net-infra/scripts/stack-config.cjs` → `STACK_GIT_REPOS`).

- Pass `--author` on every commit. Do not rely on git config (global config may be `suherman@qantas.com.au`).
- Format: `--author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>"`
- If amending a commit, always include the same `--author` flag.

```bash
git commit --author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>" -m "Short description of the change."
git log -1 --format="%an <%ae>"
git log -1 --format="%cn <%ce>"
```

After committing, verify both author and committer are `Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>`. If wrong, amend immediately:

```bash
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Iman Suherman" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="iman.suherman@gmail.com" \
  git commit --amend --author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>" --no-edit
```

## Git hooks (enforce on commit and push)

Hooks live in `suherman-net-infra/githooks/` and are installed into each repo's `.git/hooks/`:

| Hook | When | Action |
|------|------|--------|
| `prepare-commit-msg` | commit | Strip `Co-authored-by: Cursor` trailers |
| `post-commit` | commit | Auto-amend wrong author/committer or co-author lines |
| `pre-push` | push | **Reject** push if any outgoing commit has wrong identity or Cursor co-author |

Install for this repo:

```bash
npm run install-hooks
```

All stack repos:

```bash
cd ~/src/personal/suherman-net-infra
npm run install-hooks:stack
```

Also disable Cursor attribution in **Cursor Settings > Agent > Attribution** (off).
